------------
NPN surfaces
------------

NPN stands for Not (Positive & Negative).
NPN surfaces are declared as

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2 int).

    _:bng_1 {
        triples
    }

    _:bng_2 {
        triples
    }

This is equivalent with  _:bng_1 => _:bng_2
but with explicit scoping via graffiti and
using just blank nodes and RDF TriG syntax.

Declaring a positive surface:

    (graffiti) log:npn (true _:bng_2 1).

Declaring a negative surface:

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 false 1).

Declaring a neutral surface:

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 true 1).

Declaring a query:

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2 0).

Declaring a component:

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2 -1).
